                        .blurb
                            h1 "Sunlight, Tacos, and Javascript" 

                            p These are the reasons I live in  #[span Austin, Texas] where I’m working on becoming a reasonably competent web developer.  I’m an alum of the #[span University of Texas] where I studied #[span Advertising]. After graduating I joined the fantastic #[span Geographic Information Systems] program at Austin Community College.  Over those cushy years as a student, I learned to love the web and I am dedicated to pushing it forward.  My favorite libraries are #[span JQuery, Leaflet, D3, Angular, and Bootstrap#].  My preprocessing is handled by #[span Jade] and #[span Sass] and I let Codekit manage my dependencies and build procedures.  I also have experience working with #[span Object Oriented] and #[span Functional Javascript].  I live and die by my Linter. 

                            p At night I dream of keeping my #[span code dry], my #[span namespaces clean], and my #[span bandwidth cheap].  I love collaborating with others to create excellent, quality products.  Always looking to roll-up my sleeves and dig into big projects, getting my hands dirty in the digital world. But most importantly, I #[span respect the client’s resources] and my #[span team’s sanity].  I want to write code that exceeds expectations and I believe that code should be #[span Standards Compliant] and #[span Maintainable].  Caring for the big picture by handling the small details.  And improving what I already know is just as important as learning new skills.  Let’s Get to Work!    


